## Traceability Verification

### ID Chain Validation

**Chain 1: Vision → Requirements → Features → Stories → Implementation**

- [ ] Business Objective (BO-#) exists for each product area
- [ ] Each BO-# is referenced by at least one Product Feature (PRD-F-#)
- [ ] Each PRD-F-# has acceptance criteria linking to user stories
- [ ] Each US-# links back to PRD-F-# and BO-# (trace upstream)
- [ ] Each Frontend Story (FS-#) links to corresponding US-#
- [ ] Each Backend Story (BS-#) links to corresponding US-#

**Example Valid Chain:**
```
BO-1 (Business Objective: "Enable invoice creation")
  ↓
PRD-F-3 (Feature: "Create Invoice")
  ↓
US-5 (Story: "As freelancer, I can create invoice for completed work")
  ↓
FS-101 (Frontend: "Build invoice form component")
FS-102 (Frontend: "Connect form to API")
BS-201 (Backend: "POST /invoices endpoint")
DB-schema (Invoice table + constraints)
```

**Verification Status:**
- [ ] All BO-# are referenced by PRD-F-#
- [ ] All PRD-F-# are covered by US-# (no orphaned features)
- [ ] All US-# are implemented (FS-# + BS-# tasks created)
- [ ] All FS-# and BS-# link to parent US-#
- [ ] No broken reference links in traceability

### Data Entity Traceability

- [ ] All entities in erd (Entity Relationship Diagram) exist in db (Database Spec)
- [ ] All tables in db have corresponding dict (Data Dictionary) entries
- [ ] All be (Backend API) endpoints document their data inputs/outputs from dict
- [ ] All US-# acceptance criteria reference specific dict fields

**Status:** [#] / [#] traceability chains verified

