## Technical Readiness

### Non-Functional Requirements (NFRs) Verification

**Performance (nfr-4 related)**
- [ ] NFR-1: Point query response time target defined (e.g., <200ms P95)
- [ ] NFR-2: List query response time target defined (e.g., <500ms P95)
- [ ] NFR-3: API throughput target defined (e.g., 1000 req/s)
- [ ] NFR-4: Search performance target defined (e.g., full-text in <500ms)
- [ ] Actual performance measured and documented in impl (Implementation Plan)

**Scalability**
- [ ] NFR-5: Concurrent user target documented (e.g., 100 concurrent)
- [ ] NFR-6: Data volume capacity at launch and 6-month projection
- [ ] NFR-7: Growth rate accommodated in architecture

**Reliability**
- [ ] NFR-8: Uptime target defined (e.g., 99.9%)
- [ ] NFR-9: Error rate threshold defined (e.g., <0.1%)
- [ ] NFR-10: Data loss tolerance (e.g., 0 = no acceptable loss)

**Security**
- [ ] NFR-11: Authentication method chosen and documented
- [ ] NFR-12: Authorization model documented (RBAC/ABAC/other)
- [ ] NFR-13: Encryption requirements (in-transit, at-rest)
- [ ] NFR-14: PII handling strategy documented

**Maintainability**
- [ ] NFR-15: Code standards defined (linting, formatting, style guide)
- [ ] NFR-16: Test coverage target (e.g., >80%)
- [ ] NFR-17: Documentation completeness (this checklist)

**Status:** [#] / [#] NFRs quantified with targets

